    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The sections of wall of Indian temples located above but not including moldings, and below the tower or spire.  In Indian architecture, a wall; wall-frieze between vēdībandha and śikhara; kaṭi (older synonym); jāṅgha (Oriyā).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
